name: Washington Office of the Secretary of State
tweet: @kc_digiacomo All ballots submitted will be processed and it takes several weeks for the results to be finalized in a large election. Ballots mailed the day of the election are still coming in. Throughout the process, an audit trail exists for every ballot submitted.

name: Washington Office of the Secretary of State
tweet: @kc_digiacomo Once the return envelope and security envelope are separated, there is no way of telling who voted the ballot. This protects your right of absolute secrecy of the vote.

name: Washington Office of the Secretary of State
tweet: @kc_digiacomo If your ballot is challenged for any reason, the county elections department will mail a notice and give you a second opportunity to make sure your ballot counts. This is the last moment that your ballot can be associated with you.

name: Washington Office of the Secretary of State
tweet: @kc_digiacomo Counties use different ballot counting systems which may use different terms to show when your ballot is ready for counting. For example, a ballot might be accepted, received, ready for tabulation, etc.
